Sony (U.K.) Ltd said it would be doublingcapacity at its Bridgend, Wales, television and componentsfactory over the next three years in a 30 mln stg expansion.    The expansion, backed by Welsh office grants, would makeBridgend Sony's biggest tv manufacturing plant in Europe withoutput of about 500,000 tv sets per year, a spokesman said.    The move will add 300 jobs at Bridgend, bringing the totalworkforce to 1,500 at the end of the three-year period.    The expansion is part of a wider move by Sony Corp &lt;SNE.T>to locate more production capacity nearer its markets, aspokesman said. Reuter&#3;